<h2>Safety FAQs</h2>

<h3>For Users:</h3>

<h4>How can I be safer on Onestoryroad?</h4>
</br>
<p>First, don't give out your password to anyone, not even your significant other or best friend. Be sure to customize your privacy settings on the Privacy page if you are uncomfortable being found in searches or having your profile viewed by people from your school, workplace or regional network. Remember, unless you're prepared to attach something in your profile to a resume or scholarship application, don't post it.</p>
</br>
<h4>What do I do if I find an explicit, hateful or otherwise objectionable profile on Onestoryroad?</h4>
</br>
<p>We don't want any content like this on Onestoryroad. You can help us out by notifying us of any objectionable profiles. You can anonymously report offensive profile pictures and content by clicking on the "Report this Person" link located at the bottom of the profile page. You will be asked to specify the offensive content. Onestoryroad will review your complaint and will act to ensure all users comply with our Terms of Use so that Onestoryroad remains a trusted environment where people can interact safely.</p>
</br>
<h4>What do I do if I find an explicit, hateful or otherwise objectionable group on Onestoryroad?</h4>
</br>
<p>You can anonymously report offensive group pictures and content by clicking on the "Report Group" link located under the group's picture. You will be asked to specify the offensive content. Onestoryroad will review your complaint and will act to ensure all users comply with our Terms of Use so that Onestoryroad remains a trusted environment where people can interact safely.</p>
</br>
<h4>What do I do if I see something explicit, hateful, or otherwise objectionable in a "Posts" box?</h4>
</br>
<p>You can anonymously report offensive Posts by clicking on the "Report" link located under the saved material. You will be asked to specify the offensive content. Onestoryroad will review your complaint and will act to ensure all users comply with our Terms of Use so that Onestoryroad remains a trusted environment where people can interact safely.</p>
</br>
<h4>What do I do if someone has posted an objectionable photo on Onestoryroad?</h4>
</br>
<p>You can anonymously report photos that violate our Terms of Use (e.g., pornography or copyrighted images) by clicking on the "Report This Photo" link below the picture. Onestoryroad reviews these complaints and takes down photos as necessary. It is not a violation of our Terms of Use to post a photo that is unflattering, so please don't report a photo just because you don't like the way you look in it.</p>
</br>
<h4>What do I do if someone has posted a photo of me that I don't like?</h4>
</br>
<p>Onestoryroad will only remove photos that violate our Terms of Use (e.g., pornography or copyrighted images).</p>
</br>
<h4>What if I see a hateful or otherwise objectionable Note on Onestoryroad?</h4>
</br>
<p>You can anonymously report offensive note content and photos by clicking on the "Report This Note" link located below the text of each note. You will be asked to specify the offensive content. Onestoryroad will review your complaint and will act to ensure all users comply with our Terms of Use so that Onestoryroad remains a trusted environment where people can interact safely.</p>
</br>
<h4>I saw an explicit, hateful or otherwise objectionable ad on Onestoryroad. What do I do?</h4>
</br>
<p>Please email onestoryroad.com to report that ad. We will use our best efforts to remove any ads that violate our Terms of Use.</p>


<h3>For Parents:</h3>

<h4>How can I gain access to my child's account?</h4>
</br>
<p>Onestoryroad is generally forbidden by federal and many state laws to give unauthorized access to someone who is not an account holder. If you are a parent or school official, we encourage you to use software tools on your own computers to assist in overseeing your child's Internet access. Please do a search for computer-based Internet control technology on your preferred search engine to discover options that you may wish to pursue.</p>
</br>
<p>If your child is under 13 and you believe they have created a Onestoryroad account, however, the Childrens' Online Privacy Protection Act gives you the right to access personal information they have provided before Onestoryroad follows its policy of promptly deleting such data. You may access and direct the deletion of such data by having them sign into the account and then deactivating the account, or by making a request by email to Onestoryroad. Please send requests to onestoryroad.com with the subject line "COPPA Data Request".</p>
</br>
<h4>What if my child sees inappropriate content or offensive material?</h4>
</br>
<p>Onestoryroad takes the safety of its users very seriously and takes significant efforts to take down any objectionable material that may be posted on the site. We encourage users to report offensive profiles, messages, groups and photos. Reported items are then reviewed by customer support representatives and removed if deemed in violation of our Terms of Use. Users may also block others from finding them in searches, viewing their profile or sending them messages.</p>
</br>
<h4>How should I help my child use this site wisely?</h4>
</br>
<p>The best thing to do is to talk to your children and teach them Internet safety. Remind them to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Never share their password with anyone</li>
  <li>Understand their privacy settings</li>
  <li>Report people that violate our Terms of Use</li>
  <li>Block anyone that might be sending unwanted content</li>
</ul>

